-- Chennai Super Kings Beat Warriors, Win Cricket's Twenty20 Champions League
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-09-26T18:53:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-26/chennai-super-kings-beat-warriors-win-cricket-s-twenty20-champions-league.html
India’s Chennai Super Kings won
cricket’s Twenty20 Champions League following an eight-wicket
victory against South Africa’s Warriors in today’s final.  Murali Vijay  and  Michael Hussey  both scored half-centuries
for Chennai as it reached its victory target with one over
remaining in Johannesburg.  Chennai receives $2.5 million for winning the 10-team
tournament, while the Warriors collect $1.3 million.  The Warriors struggled to 128-7 from their 20 overs, with
spinners  Muttiah Muralitharan  and Ravichandran Ashwin taking
five wickets between them. Captain Davy Jacobs top-scored with
34.  In reply, Vijay and Hussey shared a 103-run opening
partnership in their team’s 132-2. Vijay scored 58, while Hussey
made 51 not out.  Mahendra Singh Dhoni  hit the winning boundary
to finish unbeaten on 17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in London at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 